text: The Eustis Lake Region was a newspaper in Eustis, Florida. The Eustis Lake Region was first published on October 23, 1884, when Eustis was still a part of Orange County, (before the lake region of Orange County became Lake County, Florida in 1887). Starting out as a weekly, after the paper was acquired by Ansil Daniel Miller it joined the Associated News Service and became a daily. ==References== Category:Publications established in 1884 Category:Weekly newspapers published in the United States Category:Daily newspapers published in the United States Category:Defunct newspapers published in Florida Category:Defunct companies based in Florida Category:1884 establishments in Florida
